22
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,920
which I think is a good sign.

23
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:29,680
Or maybe I'm too attached to it.

24
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,400
Honestly, I'm not sure, but there's only one way to find out.

25
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:36,400
I'm honestly so excited about this idea that I've been waking up every day at 6:00 a.m.

26
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,000
And I'm not usually a morning person.

27
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,040
I have my coffee.

28
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:43,040
I take a I finally get to my desk and fire up Claude Code.

29
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:47,600
And then I take a look at my to-do list and it has like a hundred things that I want to do.

30
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:52,399
Features, bug fixes, world domination, and I want to get it all done today.

31
00:01:52,399 --> 00:01:55,920
So, I start prompting Claude Code and I feel productive.

32
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:58,640
But all of a sudden, I look up at the clock and it's 1:00 p.m.

33
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,840
And what did I get done?

34
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,759
